<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="75" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="74.[151,1437,1517,1723]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1625,1651]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Remarks</emphasis>
. This is a rare species, with only one collection record from the Russian Far East (
<collectingRegion box="[1249,1429,1625,1651]" country="Russia" name="Primorskiy" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">Primorskij Kraj</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A. &amp; Taeger, A." box="[159,451,1661,1687]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="31 - 40" refId="ref78859" refString="Shinohara, A. &amp; Taeger, A. (2007) Description of a new species and collection data of pamphiliid sawflies (Insecta, Hymenoptera, Symphyta) mainly from the Russian Far East. Bulletin of the National Museum of Nature and Science, Tokyo, Series A, 33, 31 - 40." type="journal article" year="2007">Shinohara &amp; Taeger 2007</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[469,677,1661,1687]" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara (2002b)</bibRefCitation>
placed this species in his 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Shinohara" authorityYear="2002" box="[964,1108,1661,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maculosus">
<emphasis box="[964,1108,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">P. maculosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authorityName=": Kirby" authorityYear="1882" box="[1140,1234,1661,1687]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="74" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latifrons">
<emphasis box="[1140,1234,1661,1687]" italics="true" pageId="74" pageNumber="75">latifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] group emphasizing its isolated position in the genus. No molecular data for this species are available.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
